Transactions to Journalize - June

6/1 - STS issues common stock for cash investments by owners, $10,000.

6/1 - STS pays for its business license (miscellaneous expense), $50.

6/2 - STS purchases supplies (which will be used up this month) from Capital Supply Co. on account for $150.

6/6 - STS completes work for Jersey Co. and sends them an invoice for $250.

6/13 - STS pays its secretary's salary for two weeks, $600.

6/20 - STS receives a check from Nevada Corporation for the $250 on account.

6/21 - STS pays off the invoice from Office Depot from 6/10 for $40.

6/24 - STS completes work for Minnesota, Inc. and bills them on account for $750.

6/25 - STS truck expenses are $175 and the company pays all of these in cash.

6/27 - STS pays its secretary's salary for two weeks, $600.

6/30 - STS pays cash dividends of $700.
